dfischer.proxysniffer

Class ProxySnifferVarExtractorContentTokenPattern

  • java.lang.Object
    • dfischer.proxysniffer.ProxySnifferVarExtractorDataInstance
      • dfischer.proxysniffer.ProxySnifferVarExtractorContentTokenPattern

  • public class ProxySnifferVarExtractorContentTokenPattern
extends ProxySnifferVarExtractorDataInstance
    Extract the value for a var from a text-fragment of the HTTP response content by first searching a text-anchor and then by splitting the whole content into tokens.
    Since:
    V5.2-P

      • ProxySnifferVarExtractorContentTokenPattern

        public ProxySnifferVarExtractorContentTokenPattern(java.lang.String varName,
                                           java.lang.String varSourceKey,
                                           java.lang.String searchPattern,
                                           java.lang.String delimiterChars,
                                           int tokenOffsetNumber,
                                           java.lang.String recordedValue)
        Normal constructor, create an initialized instance.
        Parameters:
        varName - the name of the var
        varSourceKey - the var source key
        searchPattern - text-anchor to search
        delimiterChars - the delimiter chars used to separate the token (the value). Note that line feed(10) and carriage return(13) characters must always be part of the delimiter chars
        tokenOffsetNumber - the offset of the token to extract - relatively counted from the search pattern, this can be a positive or negative number
        recordedValue - the (old) recorded value of the token

      • findStartIndexesForRecordedValue

        public static int[] findStartIndexesForRecordedValue(java.lang.String content,
                                     java.lang.String recordedValue)
        Find all occurrences of the recorded value in the content and return an array of start indexes. Only used to support the Web GUI - not called during load test execution.
        Parameters:
        content - the whole content to which this algorithm is applied
        recordedValue - the recorded value
        Returns:
        an array of start indexes, or an empty array if the recorded value was not found

      • autoFindPossibleDelimiterSet

        public static java.lang.String[] autoFindPossibleDelimiterSet(java.lang.String content,
                                              java.lang.String recordedValue,
                                              java.lang.String optionalDelimiters)
        Calculate automatically a set containing one or more possible strings containing the delimiter chars to extract the recorded value. Only used to support the Web GUI - not called during load test execution. Note: Later - when the recorded value has to be extracted - only one of these strings is needed to use as delimiter chars.
        Parameters:
        content - the whole content to which this algorithm is applied
        recordedValue - recordedValue the recorded value
        optionalDelimiters - a string of optional delimiter chars that only will be added (additionally) to the result if they not occur in the recorded value. You can pass also null.
        Returns:
        set containing one or more possible strings containing the delimiter chars to extract the recorded value, or null if no delimiter chars are determinable

      • getUniqueSearchPatterns

        public static dfischer.proxysniffer.UniqueSearchPatternsVarExtractorContentTokenPattern getUniqueSearchPatterns(java.lang.String recordedValue,
                                                                                                java.lang.String delimiterChars,
                                                                                                java.lang.String content)
        Parse the content and get a proposition of all possible unique search patterns with their corresponding token offset number. Only used to support the Web GUI - not called during load test execution.
        Parameters:
        recordedValue - the (recorded) value of the token to extract
        delimiterChars - the delimiter chars used to separate the recorded value - pass here the result of autoConfigureDelimiterChars(String recordedValue, String content)
        content - the whole content to which this algorithm is applied
        Returns:
        A result that contains a) a list of the absolute positions of all recorded values and b) a list of all unique tokens and their absolute positions.
        See Also:
        autoConfigureDelimiterChars(String content, String recordedValue, int startIndex, String optionalDelimiters), for further GUI processing

      • extractToken

        public static java.lang.String extractToken(java.lang.String searchPattern,
                            java.lang.String delimiterChars,
                            int tokenOffsetNumber,
                            java.lang.String content)
        Implementation of the var extractor algorithm - used at runtime during load test execution.
        Parameters:
        searchPattern - text-anchor to search
        delimiterChars - the delimiter chars used to separate the extracted value (to separate the tokens). Note that line feed(10) and carriage return(13) characters must always be part of the delimiter chars
        tokenOffsetNumber - the offset of the token to extract - relatively counted from the search pattern, this can be a positive or negative number
        content - the whole content to which this algorithm is applied
        Returns:
        the extracted token, or null if no token was extracted
